32	/*! \file
33	    \brief GEMM Grouped Example.
34	
35	    This workload computes a batch of GEMM operations with distinct problem sizes. Pointers to matrices
36	    in Global Memory are passed to the kernel in array (also held in Global Memory). Similarly,
37	    leading dimensions and problem sizes are stored in arrays in GMEM.
38	
39	    This differs from "Batched Array" GEMM because the size of each GEMM problem in the Grouped GEMM
40	    concept may be distinct.
41	
42	    This benchmark program initializes a workspace with random problem sizes for a given number of
43	    groups. Command line options enable overriding M, N, and/or K dimensions with uniform values to
44	    model problems more similar to the traditional batched GEMM.
45	
46	    Additionally, problem sizes are collected and binned to compute the same problem as a series of
47	    conventional batched GEMMs (setup for this problem is not timed). This demonstrates the performance
48	    enhancement achieved by implementing a specialized grouped GEMM kernel.
49	
50	    Examples:
51	
52	      # Runs a grouped GEMM with 100 random problem sizes
53	      $ ./examples/24_gemm_grouped/24_gemm_grouped --groups=100
54	
55	      # Runs a grouped GEMM with 100 random problem sizes (with GEMM-K dimension equal to 1024)
56	      $ ./examples/24_gemm_grouped/24_gemm_grouped --groups=100 --k=1024 --verbose=true
57	
58	      # Runs a grouped GEMM that is equivalent to a batched GEMM
59	      $ ./examples/24_gemm_grouped/24_gemm_grouped --groups=100 --m=2048 --n=1024 --k=1024 --verbose=true
60	
61	      # Execute Grouped GEMM and profile with NSight
62	      $ nv-nsight-cu-cli ./examples/24_gemm_grouped/24_gemm_grouped --m=256 --n=256 --k=256 --verbose=true \
63	                                                                    --iterations=1 --reference-check=false
64	
65	*/
